</expression>
</preferred>
<definition id="_79a3b397-83a3-4b43-8687-98d84c25e415"><verbal-definition id="_c519483a-1161-ac34-5298-1aa16eeb90b2"><p id="_11863317-2c3e-5f3f-a3d8-d0b757fe3970">variety of rice whose kernels have a white and opaque appearance</p></verbal-definition></definition>


 <termnote id="_4afaf9e2-1609-fa97-db1c-d93cb68635f7"><p id="_18ba5b15-fbbf-7cde-6079-3574721a5de7">The starch of waxy rice consists almost entirely of amylopectin. The kernels have a tendency to stick together after cooking.</p>
</termnote></term>

