  <note type="Unpublished-Status"><p id="_c407dab9-1e35-3867-c718-408e1c669c01">Withdrawn.</p></note><language>en</language>
  <language>fr</language>
  <script>Latn</script>
  <abstract language="en" script="Latn">The purpose is to outline the general principles to be understood when assessing accuracy (trueness and precision) of measurement methods and results, and in applications, and to establish practical estimations of the various measures by experiment. Is concerned exclusively with measurement methods which yield measurements on a continuous scale and give a single value as the test result. May be applied to a very wide range of materials, including liquids, powders and solid objects, manufactured or naturally occurring, provided that due consideration is given to any heterogeneity of the material.</abstract>
  <status>
    <stage>95</stage>
    <substage>99</substage>
  </status>
